FBIS4-15914 "drsov071_e_94009" FBIS-SOV-94-071 Daily Report 12 Apr 1994 UKRAINE International Affairs `No More Incidents' Reported From Odessa `No More Incidents' Reported From Odessa LD1204202394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1945 GMT 12 Apr 94 LD1204202394 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Yefim Shvartsman] [Text] Odessa 12 April, TASS -- No more incidents have been reported from the 318th Division of the Black Sea Fleet to be made the 1st Brigade of the Ukrainian Navy under an order of Ukrainian Defence Minister General of the Army Vitaliy Radetskyy. Commander of the Odessa Military District Colonel-General Vladimir Shkidchenko visited the Division's First Brigade on Tuesday. Four officers and 12 warrant officers of the 318th Black Sea Fleet division said they want to serve in the Ukrainian Navy, sources told ITAR-TASS. All in all, some 200 Division officers shall decide on their further service. The officers that make a negative decision will be offered a transfer to other Russian fleets. When asked whether the officers' rights will be protected and their Odessa apartments will be left at their disposal, Shkidchenko said "none is planning deportation of the families, they will stay where they are if they want to". The new commander -- Captain 2nd Class Vladimir Marchenko -- was introduced to the Brigade personnel.
